---
title: "About the researcher"
description: |
  Ethan Ray is a PhD candiate in Industrial-Organizational Psychology at the Graduate Center, City University of New York. His research focuses on topics within employee selection and occupational health psychology with the common theme of technology integration across both domains. His employee selection research has focused on technology-mediated interviews (i.e., ), how evaluators judge these responses under various conditions and best practices for organizations adopting this technology. Topics within occupational health psychology include employee incivility both online and in person, the detrimental effects of passive leadership, and well-being outcomes from telework (i.e., working-from-home).
  
  His work has appeared in the peer reviewed *Journal of Occupational Health Psychology* and he has presented at numerous psychology conferences (e.g., SIOP, APA, IPAC). He also has experience working with Fortune 500 organizations in the areas of talent management, learning and development, assessment, performance management, and applied consulting. Ethan also teaches undergraduate courses at Baruch College including Industrial-Organizational Psychology, Research Methods in Psychology, and Statistics for the Social Sciences.
  
  Link to [Baruch College student page](https://www.iopsych-baruch.com/ethan-ray)
  
  Link to [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ethan-ray-115c)
---

